volume2_ch1: FSMs provide the initial oscillatory seeds that become attractors and proto-particles.
volume2_ch2_attractors: Proto-particles are a refined subclass of semantic attractors with reinforced identity and stability.
volume2_ch3: Proto-particles act as the main nodes in the Semantic Force Network.
volume2_ch5_proto_matter: Proto-matter is composed of aggregates of proto-particles and their fields.
volume1_ch4_mu: μ is the primary source of proto-mass for proto-particles.
volume1_ch6_lambda: λ provides curvature binding that holds proto-particles together.
volume1_ch7_psi: ψ supplies the oscillatory structure that differentiates proto-particle classes.
